cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on improving the performance of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) through data augmentation, which is a common technique used in computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning (DL) techniques, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates the performance of the CNN using various augmentation schemes, which involves optimization techniques, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a coarse-grained data set, which is a type of multimedia data, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
